\f0\b\fs52 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 4. Running Both Streams Concurrently on Windows\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 \cf0 Because your engine utilizes 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Zero-Disk RAM piping
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 , running two streams simultaneously will barely impact your hard drive or SSD. It will, however, require double the network upload speed and double the processing power.\
To run them safely together on a single Windows machine:\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774\AppleTypeServicesF393216 \cf0 {\listtext	1.	}
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Isolate Your CPU Core Affinity:
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  Windows allows you to assign specific app processes to specific CPU cores. Open your Windows Task Manager, find the two running Python instances, right-click them, select 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Set Affinity
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 , and assign Python 1 (Merry) to Cores 0\'963, and Python 2 (Mystery) to Cores 4\'967. This ensures the streams never compete for processing power or lag each other out.\
\ls3\ilvl0\AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774\AppleTypeServicesF393216 {\listtext	2.	}
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 Bitrate Optimization:
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774  Since you are running two streams, lower the streaming bitrate variable in your start_stream.bat files from 3000k down to 
\f2\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 2200k
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF2293774 . YouTube's ingestion servers will still output a crystal-clear 1080p stream for 2D art, but this slashes your home internet upload bandwidth requirements by 30%, preventing network dropouts.\
